Ensuring valid JSON structure**\\n\\nI need to make sure there are no deterministic entries in the data. It's crucial that the output remains a valid JSON object. I need to double-check the structure to ensure everything aligns with the required format. Every key and value should be correctly placed, and any surrounding syntax should be flawless to avoid any errors. This attention to detail will guarantee that the final output meets the necessary standards. Let's keep it straightforward and efficient!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Vert.x Web Client 5.0.1 is normally exercised against an HTTP server and needs no external service or extra test dependency for core coverage, but it still resolves Netty 4.2.x and the existing scaffold already documents that Netty 4.2.x needs explicit unsafe-access system properties for Java 25 native runs.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-test runtime on JDK 25, keep/apply the same Netty system properties used for 5.0.0: `-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow` and `-Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true`. Tests can use an in-process Vert.x HTTP server on localhost for meaningful WebClient coverage; no Docker service is indicated.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The current failure may be partly caused by the existing version guard applying these runtime properties only to `5.0.0`, while the reproducer runs with `GVM_TCK_LV=5.0.1`.\",\n    \"OAuth2-specific APIs reference the optional `io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2` dependency, but that is not required for meaningful core WebClient coverage unless the generated tests intentionally cover `OAuth2WebClient`.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0872ce0ae3ed1f6d016a4004b4fcc881948c3882f57191af3d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3282, "output": 765, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTo